candidate_patents.abstract:
A method of detecting cardiac interval signals in cardiologic devices comprises the following method steps: 
     time-resolved detection of cardiac events which are representative of the cardiac intervals; 
     determination of the respective cardiac interval values between two successive cardiac events; 
     statistical evaluation of a certain number of successive cardiac interval values; and 
     individual comparison of the certain number of cardiac interval values with each other such that individual cardiac interval values which deviate significantly from cardiac interval values that occur there-before and there-after are recognized as faulty measurements and corrected.
